Backport of upstream commit 5958324563 to Apache Tomcat 9.0.39 for CVE-2023-46589.

Aligns processing of trailer headers in the chunked input filter with the
standard header processing path: trailer header names must be valid tokens,
and control characters (other than HT) are rejected in trailer header
values. Also reorders the boolean operands in Http11InputBuffer.parseHeader
so the cheap HttpParser.isControl check runs before the HT comparison
(matches upstream).

The companion commits (a01d2129, b73cd85b, 485f91e3, 5a716adf) on the 9.0.x
branch are post-fix message/exception-type refinements and are intentionally
omitted: 9.0.39 predates the BadRequestException-based 400-response routing,
so this backport keeps the original IOException type used in upstream commit
5958324563. The webapps/docs/changelog.xml hunk from the upstream commit is
also omitted (documentation only, not security-relevant).

Origin: upstream, https://github.com/apache/tomcat/commit/5958324563
Author: Mark Thomas <markt@apache.org>

